House Resolution 331
By: Representative Gambill of the 15th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and legacy of Bruce Thompson, recipient of the Cartersville-Bartow
2 County Chamber of Commerce 2024 Chairman's Award; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Bruce Thompson was recently honored posthumously as the recipient of the
4 Cartersville-Bartow County Chamber of Commerce 2024 Chairman's Award in recognition
5 of his exemplary service to the State of Georgia, with his wife, Becky Thompson, accepting
6 the award on his behalf; and
7 WHEREAS, a dedicated local businessman, Bruce Thompson played an integral role in
8 Bartow County's economic growth and served as the 2012 Board Chair of the
9 Cartersville-Bartow County Chamber of Commerce; and
10 WHEREAS, he continued his service to the community as a Georgia State Senator from
11 2014 to 2022, representing parts of Bartow and Cherokee counties as well as championing
12 community values, safety, and economic development during his tenure; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2021, Bruce Thompson launched a successful campaign for Commissioner
14 of the Georgia Department of Labor, where he advanced key initiatives such as Second
15 Chance hiring and worked to position Georgia as the No. 1 state for business; and
